Court ruling impacts patient discharge process
A federal court judge has ordered Oregon State Hospital to make changes to its patient discharge process that impacts the amount of time allowed for people under aid and assist orders to remain at the hospital for competence restoration. Learn more about OSH’s implementation of the court ruling.
 
Community collaboration continues to bear fruit at JC campus
Volunteers with Eugene Area Gleaners visited the OSH Junction City campus this week to harvest the apples from trees that line the hospital’s Recovery Way entrance. Learn more about the recent harvest.
